I have proposed a refined cognitive hypothesis based on the `equally_likely` model, moving from an assumption of exactly 50% to a free subjective ideal proportion. I have written `hypothesis.md` and implemented the corresponding mechanism in `candidate.py`.

The hypothesis relies on a simple directional penalty: sequences are judged less random as the proportion of heads deviates further from the inferred `ideal_p`, which is fitted through inference. 

Both files have passed the local integrity checks ensuring PyMC variable names match the target schema correctly and the log-probability is numerically stable.
